Q4ï¸âƒ£ Validation using Setter

Goal: Allow only valid age (â‰¥18)

class User {

    // Step 1: Private data
    private int age;

    // Step 2: Setter with validation logic
    public void setAge(int age) {
        if (age >= 18) {
            this.age = age;
        } else {
            System.out.println("Age must be 18 or above");
        }
    }

    // Step 3: Getter
    public int getAge() {
        return age;
    }
}

class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {

        User u = new User();
        u.setAge(16);   // invalid
        u.setAge(22);   // valid

        System.out.println("Age: " + u.getAge());
    }
}


ðŸ§  Interview line:

Validation inside setter ensures data integrity.

ðŸŽ¯ FINAL INTERVIEW SUMMARY (MEMORIZE)

Encapsulation hides data using private variables and allows controlled access through methods like getters, setters, or business logic methods.
